-- Monsanto posts profit growth
-- 
-- Wed Apr 2, 2008 9:07am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/02/us-monsanto-results-idUSWNAS682920080402

 

 KANSAS CITY, Missouri  (Reuters) - Monsanto Co ( MON.N ) posted a higher-than-expected second-quarter profit on Wednesday, continuing to see good market share growth in corn seed and other products. 

 The agricultural products company, a global leader in the development of biotech crops, said it earned $1.79 a share for the second quarter, which ended February 29, on an ongoing basis, and $2.02 on an as-reported basis, compared with 98 cents a share a year earlier. Analysts, on average, were looking for $1.75 cents a share on an ongoing basis, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by  Carey Gillam , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)